      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:13:10",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " كَانَ عَلِيٌّ ( عليه السلام ) يَقُولُ مَنْ ضَرَبْنَاهُ حَدّاً مِنْ حُدُودِ اللَّهِ فَمَاتَ فَلَا دِيَةَ لَهُ عَلَيْنَا وَ مَنْ ضَرَبْنَاهُ حَدّاً فِي شَيْ‏ءٍ مِنْ حُقُوقِ النَّاسِ فَمَاتَ فَإِنَّ دِيَتَهُ عَلَيْنَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ibn Mahboub, from Al Hassan Bin Salih Al Sowry, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Ali<sup>asws</sup> was saying: ‘The one we<sup>asws</sup> hit the legal penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>) upon and he dies, so there is no wergild for him upon us<sup>asws</sup>, and the one we<sup>asws</sup> hit the legal penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>) upon regarding something from the rights of the people, and he dies, so his wergild is upon us<sup>asws</sup>’."
        ]
      }
